    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="664"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d664">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.111/129.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1266.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s No. 387 of July 31,
                    1913, regarding the entrance into Haiti of persons of Syrian origin, I have the
                    honor to advise the Department that I took up the matter with the President of
                    Haiti and permitted him to read the instructions of the Department on the
                    subject.</p>
                <p>The President, after reading the Department’s instructions, stated that he was in
                    full accord therewith. I have deemed it advisable, however, to have the
                    President confirm our conversation in writing and I shall endeavor to secure
                    this confirmation within the next few days.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. W. Furniss</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
